<poml>
  <meta>
    <id>agents.poml-go-sdk</id>
    <version>0.1.0</version>
    <owner>poml-go-sdk</owner>
  </meta>
  <role>Guardrails and quick pointers for automation agents working in poml-go-sdk.</role>

  <task>Respect the doc format policy.</task>
  <hint caption="Doc policy">
    <list>
      <item>Only `README.mdx` (plus `.github/copilot-instructions.md` for Copilot config) may exist as non-POML docs. Do not add other markdown/org/mdx files.</item>
      <item>All other docs belong in POML (`*.poml`) using extended tags (hint/example/cp/object/list/etc.).</item>
      <item>Link high-signal docs from README.mdx for discoverability.</item>
      <item>Repo-level Copilot guidance lives in `.github/copilot-instructions.md`; keep it aligned with these rules.</item>
    </list>
  </hint>

  <task>Know the key POML docs.</task>
  <hint caption="POML docs">
    <list>
      <item>`README.poml` — structured overview and usage guidance.</item>
      <item>`PLAN.poml` — delivery phases and milestones.</item>
      <item>`AI.LOCK.poml` — timeline/log of automated runs.</item>
      <item>`docs/fit_for_purpose.poml` — validation goals/benchmarks/checks.</item>
    </list>
  </hint>

  <task>Testing and safety.</task>
  <hint caption="Testing">
    <list>
      <item>Run `go test ./...` (CI enforces coverage threshold with coverage.out parsing).</item>
      <item>Converters enforce BaseDir containment and default 10MB image cap (override via `MaxImageBytes`).</item>
    </list>
  </hint>

  <output-format>Compact agent guidance; keep updated when policies change.</output-format>
</poml>
